'''Yasaka Shrine''' ({{ill|Yasaka Shrine|ja|八阪神社}}) in Takarazuka City is a {{ill|Shinto Shrine|ja|神社}} located in Hirai, Takarazuka, {{ill|Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県}}. It originally belonged to the village shrine system of the former Kawabe District in the village of Hirai. 

Its annual festival is celebrated with a Danjiri Festival featuring a type of ornate festival float characteristic of Takarazuka.

== Deity ==
The main deity is {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素盞嗚命}} (Susanoo-no-Mikoto), with the secondary (or co-enshrined) deity being {{ill|Hakusan-hime|ja|白山姫命}}.

== History ==
* In the early 10th century, the local tradition states that the shrine was enshrined by the children of Utsunomiya Yazasaburō Nakatsugi and Shigetuni after being invited.
* Until the Edo period, it was known as the Ushinotengū (【ill|Gyūtōtennō Shrine|ja|牛頭天王社】) dedicated to {{ill|Gyūtōtennō|ja|牛頭天王}}.
* In the second year of the Meiji period (1869), following the 【ill|Shinbutsu Bunri|ja|神仏分離令】, the enshrined deity’s name was changed to {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素盞嗚命}} and the shrine’s name was changed to Yasaka Shrine.
* In Showa 41 (1966), the shrine absorbed the Hakusan Shrine (formerly known as the Sannō Gongen Shrine) and has remained so since.

== Shrines and Grounds ==
[[File:Takarazuka-Yasaka-jinja2.jpg|thumb|Yasaka Shrine (Takarazuka City) – Haiden]]
* Main hall: A one-bay structure in the Ryūzō style built in the mid-16th century and repaired in the first year of {{ill|Jōkyō|ja|貞享}} (1684).

== Festivals and Annual Events ==
* The main festival is held around October 27 (typically on a weekend), during which a Danjiri Festival is celebrated. (This festival float is of the Takarazuka type.)

== Cultural Properties ==
* The main hall has been designated as a cultural property by Takarazuka City.

== Access ==
* A 8‑minute walk from the [[Hankyu Takarazuka Main Line]] station {{ill|Yamamoto Station|ja|山本駅}}.

== Surroundings ==
* Nearby is {{ill|Daihō-ji|ja|大宝寺}}, which—based on a syncretic arrangement—is adjacent; its wooden {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|不動明王}} and a treasure pagoda ({{ill|Hōkyōintō|ja|宝篋印塔}}) are designated cultural properties of Takarazuka City.

== References ==
{{脚注ヘルプ}}
{{Reflist}}

== See Also ==
* {{ill|Yasaka Shrine|ja|八坂神社}}
* {{ill|Gion Faith|ja|祇園信仰}}

